cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.SE 

The paper discusses data security and system efficiency in the data acquisition and transmission process in Cloud-IoT for smart grid systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, given the focus on data security and encryption, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant as they relate to distributed systems, control systems, networking, and software engineering, which are all important aspects of Cloud-IoT in smart grid systems.
